      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second analyst who confirmed boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions. A checklist-based review protocol was followed. Achieved level 2 reflects independent review without formal modeling procedure document controlled under a quality management system."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3 given the importance of contact mechanics to construct behavior.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material models with titanium alloy properties (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa) were used for all metallic components. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) was defined at screw-rod interfaces. The model form is well-established for metallic spinal implant constructs under sub-yield loading. Achieved level 3 reflects published literature support for the chosen constitutive models."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties were sourced from ASTM F136 certified material test reports for the specific lot of Ti-6Al-4V used in the experimental specimens. Geometric inputs were derived from CMM measurements of the actual test specimens. Achieved level 3 reflects traceability of inputs to specimen-specific measurements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. Specimens were from production lots with documented dimensional inspection records. Sample size provides adequate statistical power for mean comparison at the 10% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 reflects multi-laboratory, production-representative sample testing."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; this factor is below the required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 test configuration (10 degree offset angle, 35 mm moment arm). Variation in test conditions such as alternative offset angles or loading rates was not explored. Achieved level 2 reflects adherence to the standard protocol at a single condition without parametric variation, which is below the required level 3 for this model risk category."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs were mapped directly to experimentally measured specimen dimensions and material certificates. Boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture constraints including the UHMWPE block embedment. Achieved level 3 reflects documented one-to-one correspondence between model inputs and experimental parameters."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load were compared between FEA predictions and experimental measurements using mean absolute percentage error and 95% confidence intervals. Bland-Altman analysis confirmed no systematic bias. Achieved level 3 reflects quantitative statistical comparison with uncertainty characterization."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary regulatory quantities of interest for ASTM F1717 pre-market submissions for spinal fixation systems. These quantities directly support the device safety and performance claims in the 510(k) submission context. Achieved level 3 reflects direct alignment of QOIs with regulatory decision requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
